description.p:
One aspect of the present invention is a power generating apparatus of renewable energy type which generates power from a renewable energy source. The power generating apparatus may include, but is not limited to:
a rotating shaft which is driven by the renewable energy source;
a hydraulic pump which is driven by the rotating shaft;
a hydraulic motor which is driven by operating oil supplied from the hydraulic pump;
a generator which is coupled to the hydraulic motor;
an oil line which is connected to the hydraulic pump and the hydraulic motor and which circulates the operating oil between the hydraulic pump and the hydraulic motor;
an oil cooler which is connected to the oil line and which cools the operating oil by heat exchange with a cooling medium;
a cooling-medium line which supplies the cooling medium to the oil cooler;
a bypass line which diverges from at least one of the oil line and the cooling-medium line and merges into said at least one of the oil line and the cooling-medium line to bypass the oil cooler; and
a flow regulating valve which is provided in said at least one of the oil line and the cooling-medium line that is arranged between a diverging point and a merging point of the bypass line and which regulates a flow rate of at least one of the operating oil and the cooling medium flowing into the oil cooler.

claim.claim-text:
A power generating apparatus of renewable energy type which generates power from a renewable energy source, comprising:
a rotating shaft (5) which is driven by the renewable energy source;
a hydraulic pump (12) which is driven by the rotating shaft (5);
a hydraulic motor (14) which is driven by operating oil supplied from the hydraulic pump (2);
a generator (20) which is coupled to the hydraulic motor (14);
an oil line (18) which is connected to the hydraulic pump (12) and the hydraulic motor (14) and which circulates the operating oil between the hydraulic pump (12) and the hydraulic motor (14);
an oil cooler (36) which is connected to the oil line (18) and which cools the operating oil by heat exchange with a cooling medium;
a cooling-medium line (30) which supplies the cooling medium to the oil cooler (36);
characterized in that it further comprises:
a bypass line (19) which diverges from at least one of the oil line (18) and the cooling-medium line (30) and merges into said at least one of the oil line (18) and the cooling-medium line (30) to bypass the oil cooler (36); and
a flow regulating valve (51, 56) which is provided in said at least one of the oil line (18) and the cooling-medium line (30) that is arranged between a diverging point and a merging point of the bypass line (19) and which regulates a flow rate of at least one of the operating oil and the cooling medium flowing into the oil cooler (36).

Appareil de génération d'énergie du type à énergie renouvelable qui génère de l'énergie à partir d'une source d'énergie renouvelable, comportant :
un arbre rotatif (5) qui est entraîné par la source d'énergie renouvelable ;
une pompe hydraulique (12) qui est entraînée par l'arbre rotatif (5) ;
un moteur hydraulique (14) qui est entraîné par de l'huile de travail délivrée par la pompe hydraulique (2) ;
un générateur (20) qui est relié au moteur hydraulique (14) ;
une conduite d'huile (18) qui est reliée à la pompe hydraulique (12) et au moteur hydraulique (14) et qui fait circuler l'huile de travail entre la pompe hydraulique (12) et le moteur hydraulique (14) ;
un dispositif de refroidissement d'huile (36) qui est relié à la conduite d'huile (18) et qui refroidit l'huile de travail par échange de chaleur avec un fluide de refroidissement ;
une conduite de fluide de refroidissement (30) qui délivre le fluide de refroidissement au dispositif de refroidissement d'huile (36) ;
caractérisé en ce qu'il comporte en outre :
une conduite de dérivation (19) qui diverge de au moins une de la conduite d'huile (18) et de la conduite de fluide de refroidissement (30) et se raccorde à ladite au moins une de la conduite d'huile (18) et de la conduite de fluide de refroidissement (30) afin de contourner le dispositif de refroidissement d'huile (36) ; etune soupape de régulation d'écoulement (51, 56) qui est prévue dans la ladite au moins une de la conduite d'huile (18) et de la conduite de fluide de refroidissement (30) qui est disposée entre un point de divergence et un point de raccordement de la conduite de dérivation (19) et qui régule un débit d'au moins une de l'huile de travail et du fluide de refroidissement s'écoulant dans le dispositif de refroidissement d'huile (36).
